From: Byron Campen <docfaraday@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 19:11:10 -0500
Subject: (tmp-cherry-pick) Revert "Remove stringstream fallback from MakeVal
 in logging.h" (4631c1d542)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

This reverts commit 4ccdad97fcb69489aa4c77593dbc382bbd532997.

Reason for revert: In Android/iOS NDK environments std::string_view and
absl::string_view are distinct types which can end up triggering
dangling temporary pointers during conversions. StringBuilder needs to
support std::string_view directly.

Original change's description:
> Remove stringstream fallback from MakeVal in logging.h
>
> This change removes the generic MakeVal fallback in logging.h that
> relied on std::ostringstream. This hasn't been used in webrtc for years
> but now known downstream dependencies have been removed in favor of more
> efficient alternatives like StringBuilder and Abseil's string utilities.
>
> Existing call sites and related code in tests and tools have similarly
> been migrated:
>
> * Replaced std::ostringstream and std::stringstream with StringBuilder
>   in SDP, Opus, and OpenSSL unit tests.
> * Refactored string parsing in neteq_quality_test and bwe_rtp to use
>   absl::StrSplit and Abseil's numeric conversion functions.
> * Updated RTC_LOG calls in cross_traffic_unittest to explicitly load
>   atomic counters (and not rely on stringstream to do it).
> * Updated BUILD.gn and DEPS to include required Abseil and string
>   utility dependencies.
>
